<h1>Second Biggest Value</h1>

<p>In this exercise, you must compute the second maximal value contained in an array, 
 i.e. the value that becomes the maximum if you remove the current maximum from the array.</p>
 
<p>As usual, you should gather the information in only one traversal of the array.

You can assume that every values in the array are greater than <code>Integer.MIN_VALUE</code> 
 (which is the smallest representable integer existing in Java).</p>
